# {name}

A gero project. The asm-level entry point is `src/main.gas` —
edit it, then build and run with:

```bash
gero build                        # → out/debug/{name}.gx
gero run out/debug/{name}.gx
```

The `.gx` lands under a per-profile subdirectory
(`out/debug/`, `out/release/`, `out/size/`) so swapping
`[build].optimize` in `gero.toml` doesn't clobber the previous
build.

## Tests

Asm-level golden-file tests live under `tests/`. Each `tests/<name>.gas`
is paired with a `tests/<name>.expected` capturing the program's
stdout. `gero test` walks them in one pass:

```bash
gero test
gero test smoke                   # filter by name substring
```

## Format + check

Keep sources canonical and validated as you go:

```bash
gero fmt src/ tests/              # rewrite in place
gero fmt --check src/ tests/      # CI mode — exit 8 if anything would change
gero check src/ tests/            # parse + codegen-validate, no .gx written
```

## CI + pre-commit hooks

The scaffold ships no opinionated CI / hook config — that choice
is yours. Copy-paste recipes for GitHub Actions, GitLab, lefthook,
and plain git hooks live in the upstream
[gero tooling guide](https://github.com/salty-max/gero/blob/main/docs/tooling.md);
opt into the stack you prefer.
